<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/9–2248: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss>
                                at Jerusalem</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-27T17:00:00-05:00">September
                                    27, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>929. Dept has informally emphasized (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 1323 Sept 22<note n="1" xml:id="d621fn1">Not
                                printed.</note>) to Israeli rep here urgent necessity
                            demilitarization Jerusalem.<note n="2" xml:id="d621fn2">Telegram 929 was
                                repeated to Tel Aviv.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>